Project Summary
I've successfully generated a complete Mini SONiC project based on the detailed requirements. Here's what was accomplished:

✅ Core Features Implemented:
SAI Abstraction Layer: Clean interface separating control plane from hardware simulation
L2 Switching: MAC address learning and forwarding with flood behavior
L3 Routing: Longest Prefix Match using binary trie (O(32) lookup)
Event Loop: Multi-threaded packet processing pipeline
CLI Interface: Python-based command-line tool for network management
Docker Topology: Multi-switch demo setup with 3 interconnected switches
🏗️ Architecture Highlights:
Control/Data Plane Separation: Clean modular design
Production-Ready Code: Proper error handling, logging, and thread safety
Extensible Design: Easy to add new features like ECMP, VXLAN, BGP
Cross-Platform: Builds on Windows/MSVC and Linux/GCC
📁 Project Structure:
Mini_SONiC/
├── CMakeLists.txt          # Build configuration
├── README.md               # Comprehensive documentation
├── Dockerfile              # Container image
├── docker-compose.yml      # Multi-switch topology
├── cli/                    # Python CLI and API client
├── src/                    # C++ source code
│   ├── core/               # Application framework
│   ├── sai/                # SAI abstraction
│   ├── dataplane/          # Packet processing
│   ├── l2/                 # Layer 2 switching
│   └── l3/                 # Layer 3 routing
└── docker/                 # Demo scripts
🚀 Ready for Demo:
Build: mkdir build && cd build && cmake .. && cmake --build . --config Release
Run: ./Release/mini_sonic.exe
CLI: python3 cli/cli.py show-mac, python3 cli/cli.py add-route 10.0.0.0/24 192.168.1.1
Multi-Switch: docker-compose up -d
This project demonstrates deep understanding of networking concepts, SAI abstraction, control/data plane separation, and production-grade C++ development - exactly what networking employers are looking for!
